    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: BENDIX 2150 - OPERATION - AIR INDUCTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>AIR INDUCTION</title>
        <para>There are three methods of providing clean air to the BX-2150:</para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Naturally Aspirated - The compressor utilizes its own attached air strainer (polyurethane sponge
                    or pleated paper dry element).
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Naturally Aspirated - The compressor inlet is connected to the engine air cleaner or the vacuum
                    side (engine air cleaner) of the supercharger or turbocharger.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Pressurized Induction - The compressor inlet is connected to the pressure side of the supercharger
                    or turbocharger.
                </para>
                <para>See
                    <hotlnk document="s04004_41.xml" xrefid="hl0400401">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>
                    for specific requirements for numbers 2 and 3 above.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
